  "decision_conditions": [
    "REASON: The proposed rear first floor rear extension by reason of its inappropriate design, scale, rearward depth, bulk, massing and height would form a dominant and discordant addition to the rear of the host property and wider terrace setting, which would be exacerbated by the two large and unsympathetic rear windows. The proposal would be visible from the surrounding public and private realm.  The proposal is therefore considered to be contrary to Policies D4 and HC1 the London Plan 2021, Policies CS8 and CS9 of the Core Strategy 2011 and Policies DM2.1 and DM2.3 of the Development Management Policies 2013. It also contravenes the guidance within the Urban Design Guide 2017, the Chapel Market/Penton Street Conservation Area Design Guidance and the NPPF 2021."
